  "texts": [
    "Such information is vital for inferring the likely subsequent actions of the partner agent.",
    "Location of the Agent Controlled by LLM:Given the limitations of Large Language Models (LLMs) in interpreting grid-based spatial information, we opt to provide processed location data to the LLM.",
    "For each agent P i (where i ∈ {1, 2}), and for each location of interest denoted as loc, we calculate the distance d (P i,loc) as the number of steps required to reach loc from P i using the shortest available path.",
    "The state description D(S) then includes this processed location information in the format: \"loc is d (P i,loc) units away.\"",
    "Here, loc can represent various points of interest such as onion dispensers, plate dispensers, cookers, delivery areas, kitchen counters, or shared counters."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}